Write a function safeNumber that takes an integer x, returns true if x contains a safe integer value, and false otherwise.

Examples:

safeNumber (20000) must return true;
safeNumber (9007199254740991) must return true;
safeNumber (9007199254740992) must return false.

Solution:

function safeNumber(x){
  return Number.isSafeInteger(x);
}
